Return one JSON object. No prose. No analysis.

The object must have exactly one key: items.
items must be an array with one object per image.

For each image object, use exactly these keys:
image_path, tag_text, category_type, manufacturer, brand, product_name, weight, unit, packaging_type, country_of_origin, promotional_messages, variant, fragrance_flavor, addons, tagline.

Rules:
- Set image_path to the exact Image Path provided before that image.
- Do not extract barcode. Barcode is decoded separately after grouping.
- tag_text is the dataset label printed around the image border, often beginning with GH. Copy it exactly enough for grouping.
- category_type: short product type, e.g. MARGARINE, MAYONNAISE, BUTTER, JUICE.
- variant: product variant if visible, e.g. ORIGINAL, LOW FAT. Use null if not on label.
- fragrance_flavor: flavor or fragrance if visible, e.g. RICH, VANILLA. Use null if not on label.
- addons: extra pack contents if mentioned, e.g. SPOON INCLUDED. Use null if absent.
- tagline: short promotional or descriptive tagline if visible. Use null if absent.
- promotional_messages: on-pack promotion text, e.g. 50% OFF. Use null if absent.
- Extract only fields visible in that specific image.
- Use null for fields that are not visible or unclear.
- Do not merge information across images.
- Do not guess.

Example shape:
{
  "items": [
    {
      "image_path": "data/uploads/example.jpg",
      "tag_text": "GH000000 Product Front",
      "category_type": null,
      "manufacturer": null,
      "brand": null,
      "product_name": null,
      "weight": null,
      "unit": null,
      "packaging_type": null,
      "country_of_origin": null,
      "promotional_messages": null,
      "variant": null,
      "fragrance_flavor": null,
      "addons": null,
      "tagline": null
    }
  ]
}
